"title": "5418: monotony",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5418",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The sameness that arises through dull and wearisome routines, and which cause individuals to feel bored. Scripture often portrays monotony as a cause of sin, in that individuals, in seeking excitement, often fall into sinful practices.</p>\n<h2>Monotony can give rise to sin</h2>\n<h3>Discontent in the desert</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:4-Num11:6\">NUM 11:4–11:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:2-Exod16:3\">EXO 16:2–16:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:35\">EXO 16:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:33\">NUM 14:33</a> <em>The monotony of 40 years in the desert was a judgment on Israel's unbelief.</em></p>\n<h3>At Sinai impatience leads to idolatry</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:1\">EXO 32:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:23\">EXO 32:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:40\">ACT 7:40</a></p>\n<h2>Situations which give rise to monotony</h2>\n<h3>Desert</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps107:4-Ps107:5\">PSA 107:4–107:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:19\">DEU 1:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:30\">ISA 40:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:12-Mark1:13\">MRK 1:12–1:13</a></p>\n<h3>Prison</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps107:10\">PSA 107:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg16:21\">JDG 16:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps66:11\">PSA 66:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer38:6\">JER 38:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:12\">MAT 4:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:10\">REV 2:10</a></p>\n<h3>Illness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps107:17-Ps107:18\">PSA 107:17–107:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:15-Lev26:16\">LEV 26:15–26:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job30:16-Job30:17\">JOB 30:16–30:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps6:3\">PSA 6:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:11\">LUK 13:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:5\">JHN 5:5</a></p>\n<h3>Storm at sea</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps107:25-Ps107:26\">PSA 107:25–107:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah2:3\">JON 2:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts27:27\">ACT 27:27</a></p>\n<h3>Darkness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps143:3\">PSA 143:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod10:22\">EXO 10:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps130:6\">PSA 130:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:33\">MRK 15:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:8\">LUK 2:8</a></p>\n<h3>Work</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:17-Gen3:19\">GEN 3:17–3:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job7:2\">JOB 7:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:11\">ECC 2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:9\">GAL 6:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:2-Rev2:3\">REV 2:2–2:3</a></p>\n<h3>Siege</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs6:25\">2KI 6:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:2\">2KI 25:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa36:12\">ISA 36:12</a></p>\n<h3>Slavery</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:23\">EXO 2:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job7:2\">JOB 7:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:1\">1TI 6:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:18\">1PE 2:18</a></p>\n<h3>Sleeplessness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job7:4\">JOB 7:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth6:1\">EST 6:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job30:17\">JOB 30:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl5:12\">ECC 5:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:18\">DAN 6:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:3\">HEB 12:3</a></p>\n<h2>Monotony arising from difficult human relations</h2>\n<h3>A nagging wife</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:13\">PRO 19:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov27:15\">PRO 27:15</a></p>\n<h3>Unhelpful counsellors</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job6:6\">JOB 6:6</a></strong> <em>This refers to the useless advice of Job's friends.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col4:6\">COL 4:6</a> <em>This, by contrast, is how the conversation of Christians is to be characterised.</em></p>",
